# Lin Language TODO
# Format: [ ] pending  [/] in progress  [x] done
# Tiers: 🔴 blocking  🟡 important  🟢 nice-to-have

# Architecture reference:
#   pic.graph  → abstract combinator graph (γ⁺ γ⁻ δ ε ω + boundaries)
#   pic.reduce → scheduling-aware reduction ops (annihilate/dup/erase/fire_op)
#   pic.runtime→ CPU/GPU dispatch (cpu_dispatch, gpu_batch, sync_point)
#
# Node set (5 nodes):
#   γ⁺  Constructor  principal(+), aux(left, right)
#   γ⁻  Destructor   principal(-), aux(left, right)
#   δ   Duplicator   principal(*), aux(left, right)
#   ε   Eraser       principal(*), no aux
#   ω   Operation    principal(+/-), aux(inputs..., outputs...)
#
# 4 Rules: Annihilation, Duplication, Erasure, Congruence
# Rules should be mostly user-defined via a lookup table.

## 🔴 Tier 1 — Architecture (core correctness)

[/] A1. pic.reduce pass: implement the actual reduction rules
        - PicReduceToRuntimePass::runOnOperation() is currently a no-op {}
        - Should emit pic_reduce.annihilate / duplicate / erase / fire_op ops
          for each active pair detected in pic.graph
        - This is the CPU/GPU parity linchpin: rules defined here lower to
          both LLVM (CPU) and SPIR-V (GPU) via standard MLIR lowerings

[ ] A2. Rule lookup table (user-extensible dispatch)
        - Currently: hardcoded if-else CondBrOp chain in worker_thread builder
        - Should be: table keyed on (agentType_A, label_A, agentType_B, label_B)
          → rule function pointer / pic_reduce op
        - Enables user-defined reduction rules from .lin code
        - GPU: same table, different lowering target

[/] A3. Fix γ⁺/γ⁻ encoding for function agents
        - NODE_FN=5 / NODE_APP=6 are wrong per PIC spec
        - Function definition = γ⁺ (constructor), application = γ⁻ (destructor)
        - They should annihilate via the standard Rule 1 (same-type annihilation)
        - The "beta block" we added is just annihilation in disguise — collapse it
        - The label (function name) encodes which function, not the node type

[ ] A4. Boundary [ ] lowering
        - BoundaryOp is declared in PicGraphDialect.td but not lowered
        - Needed for: E-graph congruence (Rule 4), effect scoping (B1-B3)
        - MLIR regions map naturally to boundaries
        - Lowering: boundary dissolves when inner graph fully reduces

## 🔴 Tier 1 — Language Semantics (blocking for correct execution)

[ ] 1. AST_PAIR lowering in lowerExpression
        - Emit a pair agent that holds two ports
        - Wire left/right sub-expressions into p1/p2
        - Field access (.0 / .1) selects p1 or p2 via a δ-split agent

[x] 2. `either` reduction rule (if/else at runtime)
        - CPU worker_thread: BRANCH ~ NUM fires, selects true/false port, erases loser
        - NODE_BRANCH=7 added to node type encoding (to be collapsed into ω later)
        - TODO(A3): should be ω(+, branch) ⋈ ω(-, branch) op annihilation
        - TODO(A1): GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass

[/] 3. Beta-reduction rule (function application at runtime)
        - Phase 1: γ(+,f) ~ δ(-,f) wires aux ports (p1↔p1, p2↔p2)
        - TODO(A3): should be γ⁺ ⋈ γ⁻ standard annihilation — no separate beta block needed
        - TODO(A1): GPU kernel parity via unified pic.reduce pass

[ ] 4. mlir-op full pipeline connection
        - User-declared mlir-op in .lin files should register to the rule lookup table (A2)
        - ω(+, f) ⋈ ω(-, f) → fires the MLIR payload for label f

## 🟡 Tier 2 — Language Completeness

[ ] 5. Closure / captured variable support
        - Thread outer-scope bindings into inner γ⁺ function agents via aux ports
        - Sharing → δ (duplicator) nodes for multi-use bindings

[ ] 6. Binary operator coverage
        - Add TOKEN_STAR (*), TOKEN_SLASH (/), TOKEN_GREATER (>),
          TOKEN_GREATER_EQUAL (>=), TOKEN_EQUAL_EQUAL (==),
          TOKEN_NOT_EQUAL (!=), TOKEN_AND (&&), TOKEN_OR (||)
        - All map to ω agents with appropriate MLIR op labels

[ ] 7. Type checking / type-directed dispatch
        - Use AstFuncArg.type_name for lightweight structural checking
        - Emit type mismatch errors with source locations
        - Type-directed code gen (e.g., i32 add vs. f32 fadd via ω label)

[ ] 8. Multiple return values via pairs
        - Once AST_PAIR lowering (#1) works, ensure function return types
          can be pairs and that .0 / .1 access compiles correctly

## 🟢 Tier 3 — Developer Experience

[ ] 9.  `linc run` command
        - Compile to temp binary and execute in one step

[ ] 10. @gpu / @cpu per-function annotations
        - Parser: recognize @identifier annotations
        - pic.reduce → pic.runtime routing based on annotation attr
        - No pragma needed: graph structure encodes parallelism by default

[ ] 11. Human-readable error messages
        - Source location (file:line:col) on parse errors

[ ] 12. Node GC / arena reset
        - Erasure propagation IS GC (Rule 3 parallel ε sweep)
        - Arena reset for long-running programs

## 🔵 Architecture — Unified Pipeline

[ ] 13. Unified CPU/GPU reduction pipeline via pic.reduce
        - Implement PicReduceToRuntimePass: pic.reduce ops → cpu_dispatch / gpu_batch
        - CPU path: lower pic_reduce.annihilate → LLVM atomic store/GEP sequence
        - GPU path: lower pic_reduce.annihilate → gpu.launch / spirv ops
        - Eliminates the LLVM IR builder duplication in PicRuntimeToLLVMPass
        - Marked in code with TODO(unified-pipeline)
        - This is the path to shader support (CPU / general GPU / high-perf GPU)

[ ] 14. 128-bit node layout audit
        - Current: int32_t[4] per node (128 bits — correct size)
        - Verify field encoding matches spec: principal port as atomic bit-field
        - Polarity encoded in port value, not separate field
        - Enables lock-free redex detection via single atomic CAS

[ ] 15. Congruence / E-graph rule (Rule 4)
        - Inside boundaries: hash normal forms, merge identical subgraphs
        - Fires continuously during reduction (not a post-pass)
        - Integrate with boundary lowering (A4)
